The user confirmed the MVP dashboard is working perfectly and live data is streaming. I will celebrate this milestone and present options for the next logical phase of the project (e.g., historical data import, more graphs, or settings UI).\n\n> [!STRATEGY]\n> **Intent:** Celebrate the MVP success and propose the next phase of development based on the implementation plan.","description":"Update topic to: \"Planning Next Phase\"","displayName":"Update Topic Context","renderOutputAsMarkdown":true}]}
{"id":"3ef1e747-9b88-41a9-b89f-ab08b4931cee","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:15:25.492Z","type":"gemini","content":"That is fantastic to hear! There's nothing quite like seeing live data from the physical world suddenly populating a native desktop app you just built. \"Mount Soledad South\" is officially streaming to CumulusAI!\n\nNow that we have a functional MVP capturing real-time WebSocket data, storing it in SQLite, and rendering it to the UI, we get to decide what part of the `CumulusAI_Implementation_Plan.md` we want to tackle next. \n\nHere are the most logical next steps to choose from:\n\n**Option 1: The Time Machine (Historical Data Import)**\nRight now, the app only knows about the weather from the moment you opened it. We can build the **Cumulus Importer** (Phase 2) to read your 8+ years of legacy data (`dayfile.txt` and `*log.txt`), or the **MDB Importer** to pull from the Access database. This will instantly fill out your \"Records\" and let you scroll the graph back in time.\n\n**Option 2: Dashboard Expansion (Phase 3 & 5)**\nWe can calculate the derived values (Heat Index, Wind Chill, Dew Point) and add the remaining graphs (Pressure trend lines, Wind Rose, Rain bars) so the dashboard looks completely fleshed out.\n\n**Option 3: The Settings & Calibration Hub (Phase 7)**\nWe can build out the GUI Settings Dialog so you can manage those API keys without touching the code, set up your units (F/C, inHg/hPa), and implement the sensor calibration offsets that the original Cumulus software used.\n\nWhich direction sounds the most fun to you right now?","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":59011,"output":349,"cached":53442,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":59360},"model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}
{"$set":{"lastUpdated":"2026-05-09T17:15:25.493Z"}}
