{"id":"df22d8fd-8f30-43c4-a40f-d4ced8b8d370","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:10:17.368Z","type":"user","content":[{"text":"I love the tracer-bullet idea!  Thanks for teaching me that.  \nI also love the idea of coding in Rust.  Everything I've done since I started coding with LLMs in Nov 25 has been Python (with SQL, Typescript in the mix, too).  So writing in Rust would be so geeky cool.  Your general plan is right on target, friend.  The one thing we haven't talked about, though it is in the project notes, is the idea of using all this location-specific data in conjunction with the power of LLMs to do some AI-based weather forecasting for Mount Soledad, La Jolla.  All that data is from the exact same spot on Earth.  Granted, 17 years of data isn't a ton, but it's not bad.  So that Phase 4 project is where the idea for CumulusAI comes in."}]}
