{"id":"6e4db1fb-2abe-478c-b32d-c75142553c42","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:28:13.258Z","type":"gemini","content":"I have successfully moved `main.py`, `requirements.txt`, and the `cumulusai/` folder into an `Archive_TracerBullet/` folder to keep your root directory clean. \n\nI also created `CumulusAI_Vision_and_Architecture_v2.md` at the root of the project. It captures our entire discussion: the \"Fish Tank\" vs. \"Analyst\" modes, the 5 distinct phases, the tech stack (Tauri/React/Rust/Python-Sidecar), and the AI Oracle capstone for Mount Soledad.\n\n*(Note: My image reader tripped over a `.gitignore` rule for the `Legacy` folder so I couldn't pull up the exact JPG you linked, but between your Bermuda description and my internal knowledge of vintage barographs—the glass case, the brass mechanical arm, the grid paper drum—I know exactly the aesthetic we are chasing!)*\n\nWe now have a beautifully clean slate.\n\nIf you are ready to pour the foundation for Phase 1, the command to scaffold the entire modern application is:\n\n```powershell\nnpm create tauri-app@latest\n```\n\nThis is an interactive command. It will ask you for a project name (I suggest `cumulus-dashboard`), and then you can select **React** and **TypeScript** from the menus.\n\nLet me know once you've run it, and we can take our first steps into Rust!","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":70258,"output":301,"cached":0,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":70559},"model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}
