{"id":"e1d02cbe-319f-4186-b987-89c66813333c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:37:04.184Z","type":"gemini","content":"You should run it directly in your **`G:\\Dev\\CumulusAI`** directory. \n\nHere is exactly what it will do: it is *not* a global installation to your C: drive. The `npm create` command fetches the latest scaffolding template and builds a brand new, self-contained project folder right where you run it.\n\nSo, in your PowerShell window:\n\n1. Ensure you are at `G:\\Dev\\CumulusAI>`.\n2. Run `npm create tauri-app@latest`\n\nThe interactive prompts will look like this:\n\n*   **Project name:** I recommend `cumulus-dashboard` (this will create a folder named `G:\\Dev\\CumulusAI\\cumulus-dashboard`).\n*   **Choose which language to use for your frontend:** Select `TypeScript / JavaScript`\n*   **Choose your package manager:** Select `npm`\n*   **Choose your UI template:** Select `React`\n*   **Choose your UI flavor:** Select `TypeScript`\n\nOnce it finishes, it will give you three commands to `cd` into that new folder, install the packages, and run the empty app. Let me know when you see the default Tauri welcome window!","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":68616,"output":256,"cached":61693,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":68872},"model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}
