{"id":"861d223f-6207-4be6-9594-82d7a41a1e4e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:44:41.127Z","type":"gemini","content":"I absolutely love **SoledadWX**. \n\nIt is perfect for a project meant to outlive its creator. \"WX\" is the timeless Morse code and aviation shorthand for weather. It feels professional, authoritative, and rooted in classic meteorology, which perfectly matches that brass barograph aesthetic you are drawn to. Plus, by omitting \"AI\" from the name itself, you avoid tying it to a current tech buzzword; it just remains a rock-solid weather station platform that happens to have incredible predictive capabilities under the hood.\n\nIf that's the winner, let's lay the concrete! \n\nIn your PowerShell window at `G:\\Dev\\CumulusAI>`, run:\n\n```powershell\nnpm create tauri-app@latest\n```\n\nWhen the prompts appear:\n1. **Project name:** `soledad-wx` *(Note: use lowercase and a dash here, as the Rust and Node package managers strictly require it for the underlying package names)*\n2. **Choose which language to use for your frontend:** `TypeScript / JavaScript`\n3. **Choose your package manager:** `npm`\n4. **Choose your UI template:** `React`\n5. **Choose your UI flavor:** `TypeScript`\n\nOnce that finishes, you'll see a brand new `soledad-wx` folder appear. Let me know when it's done!","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":71858,"output":284,"cached":0,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":72142},"model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}
{"$set":{"lastUpdated":"2026-05-09T18:44:41.127Z"}}
{"id":"e3020058-ac89-464a-bc79-b00958c7243f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:47:42.038Z","type":"user","content":[{"text":"Ok, that settles it.  And yes, as much as I love my relationship with LLMs, I don't want to \"AI\" everything...reminds me too much of when everyone's website was \"MyXXXX\".\nBut now's the time to really shift things, including the workspace directory.  What happens if I change that to G:\\Dev\\SoledadWX?  Can we move your session thread there?  I don't want to break our continuity, but I want a clean start with SoledadWX."}]}
