{"id":"92a02c19-c247-40c6-bd8f-2d3c4c6df546","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:50:36.128Z","type":"gemini","content":"Yes, the CLI stores its session data in your user profile (specifically, under `C:\\Users\\Morpheus\\.gemini\\tmp\\cumulusai`). \n\nHowever, because the CLI ties that history to the specific workspace folder path (`G:\\Dev\\CumulusAI`), when you launch it from the new `G:\\Dev\\SoledadWX` folder, it will likely treat it as a brand new workspace and start a fresh session.\n\nTo make this completely bulletproof and seamless, I just renamed our planning document to **`SoledadWX_Architecture.md`**. All of our brilliant ideas, the 5 phases, the \"fish tank\", and the AI oracle are safely saved in that markdown file.\n\nHere is the flawless handoff procedure:\n\n1. Type `/exit` right here and hit enter. (This kills my process and releases the Windows folder lock).\n2. Rename the folder from `CumulusAI` to `SoledadWX` in File Explorer.\n3. Open your terminal in the new `G:\\Dev\\SoledadWX` folder.\n4. Launch the CLI again.\n5. Paste this exact message to \"new\" me:\n\n> *\"We just renamed the project to SoledadWX. Read the `SoledadWX_Architecture.md` file to catch up on our 5-phase plan, and let's run the Tauri scaffold!\"*\n\nThe \"new\" me will read the doc, instantly sync up with our entire conversation, and we won't miss a single beat. \n\nSee you on the other side in the new `SoledadWX` folder! Type `/exit` when you're ready!","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":71010,"output":350,"cached":68479,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":71360},"model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}
